com.emc.atmos.api.request

Class ListMetadataRequest<T extends ListMetadataRequest<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.emc.atmos.api.request.Request
      • com.emc.atmos.api.request.ListRequest<T>
        • com.emc.atmos.api.request.ListMetadataRequest<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Represents the implementation type. Allows a consistent builder interface throughout the request hierarchy. Parameterize concrete subclasses with their own type and implement ListRequest.me() to return "this". In abstract subclasses, return me() in builder methods.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ListDirectoryRequest, ListObjectsRequest

    public abstract class ListMetadataRequest<T extends ListMetadataRequest<T>>
extends ListRequest<T>
    Represents common elements of list requests that may include object metadata.

      • setSystemMetadataNames

        public void setSystemMetadataNames(java.util.List<java.lang.String> systemMetadataNames)
        Sets the list of system metadata names that will be returned for each object in the list. If null, all system metadata will be returned for each object in the list.

      • setIncludeMetadata

        public void setIncludeMetadata(boolean includeMetadata)
        Sets whether the resulting list should include metadata for each object. Note that the default page size for result lists changes when you include metadata in the results. Most Atmos systems default to 10k objects per page without metadata and 500 with.
